==English==
===Pronunciation===
*(''[[RP]]''): /sɒft siː/, /<tt>sQft si:</tt>/
*(''US''): säft sē, /sɑːft siː/, /<tt>sA:ft si:</tt>/

===Noun===
'''soft c'''

#{{linguistics}} In many languages, a letter "c" which is not pronounced as a [[velar]] [[stop]] (/k/, like English "k") but as a [[sibilant]] (/s/, like English "s") or an [[affricative]] (/tʃ/, like English "ch"). 
'''Examples'''
#In English, the "c" sound in "cent", "central" and "circuit" as distinct from the [[hard c]] in "cat" and "cabin".
#In Italian, the "c" sound in "[[certo]]" as distinct from the "c" sound in "[[caffè]]".  

